{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775850851504,"sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","part":{"id":"prt_d78f58caf00188Wc90nC2X8BI3","messageID":"msg_d78f580b0001ZKONp2tAZekp58","sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775850857181,"sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","part":{"id":"prt_d78f59c39001GGEP7y70wzjuGN","messageID":"msg_d78f580b0001ZKONp2tAZekp58","sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture of the project structure. Let me write the proposal for AR-007 — K8s Reconciler Controller. I'll update the proposal.md to replace AR-006 with AR-007 since this is a new proposal task.","time":{"start":1775850857177,"end":1775850857177}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775850989105,"sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","part":{"id":"prt_d78f67ec40014LTWiCcGGjexSB","messageID":"msg_d78f580b0001ZKONp2tAZekp58","sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","type":"text","text":"Runtime","time":{"start":1775850989099,"end":1775850989099}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850989183,"sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","part":{"id":"prt_d78f5a2db001xU6YFU9wRMr1hR","messageID":"msg_d78f580b0001ZKONp2tAZekp58","sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler Controller\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller in `pkg/workloadmanager` that watches and reconciles `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources. This controller uses the generated client-go library to provide robust, event-driven reconciliation of sandbox lifecycle states, ensuring the actual state of sandbox pods matches the desired state defined in the CRs.\n\nThe reconciler handles CR creation, updates, and deletion events; manages Pod lifecycle through the Kubernetes API; updates CR status with observed state; and implements requeue logic for transient failures. It integrates with the WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework (AR-004) and provides the core control loop for the AgentCube platform.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| **CRDs managed** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) |\n| **Controller types** | `AgentRuntimeReconciler`, `CodeInterpreterReconciler` |\n| **Core functionality** | Event-driven reconciliation, status updates, Pod lifecycle management, finalizer handling, requeue with backoff |\n| **Integration with** | client-go generated clientset (typed client), informers (cache), Store (Redis) for session sync |\n| **Error handling** | Requeue on transient errors, permanent failure marking, exponential backoff, rate limiting |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- CRD definition and schema (already defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`)\n- client-go library generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n- HTTP server framework itself (AR-004)\n- Store implementation details (external dependency)\n- Multi-cluster reconciliation\n- Custom metrics server (separate component)\n- Webhook validation/mutation (separate AR)\n- Helm chart modifications\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/controller.go` | **NEW** — Controller manager, shared informer factory setup, graceful shutdown |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_reconciler.go` | **NEW** — `AgentRuntimeReconciler` implementation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_reconciler.go` | **NEW** — `CodeInterpreterReconciler` implementation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go` | **NEW** — Base `Reconciler` interface and common utilities |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/queue.go` | **NEW** — Rate-limited work queue with exponential backoff |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/finalizer.go` | **NEW** — Finalizer management utilities |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/metrics.go` | **NEW** — Reconciliation metrics (attempts, latency, errors) |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/types.go` | **NEW** — Controller-specific type definitions |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`Reconciler` interface** — Common reconciler contract:\n\n```go\n// Reconciler is the interface implemented by all CR reconcilers.\ntype Reconciler interface {\n    // Reconcile processes a single resource and returns the result.\n    // key is the namespace/name of the resource.\n    Reconcile(ctx context.Context, key string) (Result, error)\n    \n    // Name returns the reconciler name for logging/metrics.\n    Name() string\n}\n\n// Result contains the outcome of a reconciliation.\ntype Result struct {\n    // Requeue indicates whether to requeue the key for later processing.\n    Requeue bool\n    \n    // RequeueAfter specifies the duration to wait before requeuing.\n    // Zero means use default backoff.\n    RequeueAfter time.Duration\n    \n    // TerminalError indicates a non-recoverable error occurred.\n    TerminalError bool\n}\n```\n\n**`AgentRuntimeReconciler`** — Reconciler for AgentRuntime CRs:\n\n```go\n// AgentRuntimeReconciler reconciles AgentRuntime custom resources.\ntype AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n    // client is the generated typed client for runtime/v1alpha1\n    client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n    \n    // podClient is the corev1 pod client for sandbox pod management\n    podClient corev1.PodInterface\n    \n    // informer caches AgentRuntime objects\n    informer cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    \n    // lister provides cached read access to AgentRuntimes\n    lister runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n    \n    // storeClient syncs session state with Redis/Valkey\n    storeClient store.Interface\n    \n    // recorder emits Kubernetes events\n    recorder record.EventRecorderLogger\n    \n    // workqueue holds keys to be reconciled\n    workqueue workqueue.RateLimitingInterface\n}\n```\n\n**`CodeInterpreterReconciler`** — Reconciler for CodeInterpreter CRs:\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterReconciler reconciles CodeInterpreter custom resources.\ntype CodeInterpreterReconciler struct {\n    client    runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n    podClient corev1.PodInterface\n    informer  cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    lister    runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n    storeClient store.Interface\n    recorder  record.EventRecorderLogger\n    workqueue workqueue.RateLimitingInterface\n}\n```\n\n**`ControllerManager`** — Manages all reconcilers and shared infrastructure:\n\n```go\n// ControllerManager coordinates all reconcilers and shared informers.\ntype ControllerManager struct {\n    // sharedInformerFactory provides cached informers for all types\n    sharedInformerFactory externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n    \n    // reconcilers holds all registered reconcilers\n    reconcilers []Reconciler\n    \n    // stopCh signals shutdown to all controllers\n    stopCh chan struct{}\n    \n    // wg waits for all goroutines to finish\n    wg sync.WaitGroup\n    \n    // healthHandler provides readiness/liveness probes\n    healthHandler health.Handler\n}\n```\n\n### Reconciliation Flow\n\n```\nInformer event (Add/Update/Delete)\n  → Add key to workqueue\n    → Worker picks up key\n      → Get object from lister (cache)\n        → Reconcile()\n          1. Check if CR is being deleted (deletion timestamp set)\n             → Handle finalizer cleanup\n          2. Ensure finalizer is present (if not deleting)\n          3. Sync sandbox Pod state with CR spec\n             → Create Pod if not exists\n             → Update Pod if spec changed\n          4. Update CR status with observed state\n             → Set Phase, Conditions, SandboxID, PodName, PodIP\n          5. Sync session state with Store\n          6. Return Result (requeue if needed)\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime Reconciliation Logic\n\n```go\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, key string) (Result, error) {\n    namespace, name, err := cache.SplitMetaNamespaceKey(key)\n    if err != nil {\n        return Result{TerminalError: true}, err\n    }\n    \n    // Get CR from cache\n    ar, err := r.lister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)\n    if err != nil {\n        if errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n            // Object deleted, cleanup already handled via finalizer\n            return Result{}, nil\n        }\n        return Result{Requeue: true}, err\n    }\n    \n    // Handle deletion\n    if ar.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n        return r.handleDeletion(ctx, ar)\n    }\n    \n    // Ensure finalizer\n    if !controllerutil.ContainsFinalizer(ar, AgentRuntimeFinalizer) {\n        controllerutil.AddFinalizer(ar, AgentRuntimeFinalizer)\n        _, err := r.client.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update(ctx, ar, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n        return Result{Requeue: true}, err\n    }\n    \n    // Sync Pod\n    pod, err := r.getOrCreatePod(ctx, ar)\n    if err != nil {\n        r.updateStatus(ctx, ar, AgentRuntimePhaseFailed, \"PodCreationFailed\", err.Error())\n        return Result{Requeue: true, RequeueAfter: 5 * time.Second}, err\n    }\n    \n    // Update status based on Pod state\n    switch pod.Status.Phase {\n    case corev1.PodPending:\n        r.updateStatus(ctx, ar, AgentRuntimePhasePending, \"PodPending\", \"\")\n        return Result{Requeue: true, RequeueAfter: 2 * time.Second}, nil\n    case corev1.PodRunning:\n        r.updateStatus(ctx, ar, AgentRuntimePhaseRunning, \"PodRunning\", \"\")\n        // Sync with Store\n        r.syncStore(ctx, ar, pod)\n        return Result{}, nil\n    case corev1.PodSucceeded:\n        r.updateStatus(ctx, ar, AgentRuntimePhaseSucceeded, \"PodCompleted\", \"\")\n        return Result{}, nil\n    case corev1.PodFailed:\n        r.updateStatus(ctx, ar, AgentRuntimePhaseFailed, \"PodFailed\", pod.Status.Message)\n        return Result{}, nil\n    }\n    \n    return Result{}, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Finalizer Handling\n\n```go\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) handleDeletion(ctx context.Context, ar *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (Result, error) {\n    if !controllerutil.ContainsFinalizer(ar, AgentRuntimeFinalizer) {\n        return Result{}, nil\n    }\n    \n    // Delete associated Pod\n    podName := ar.Status.PodName\n    if podName != \"\" {\n        err := r.podClient.Pods(ar.Namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{\n            PropagationPolicy: ptr.To(metav1.DeletePropagationBackground),\n        })\n        if err != nil && !errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n            return Result{Requeue: true}, err\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Cleanup Store session\n    if ar.Status.SandboxID != \"\" {\n        r.storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, ar.Status.SandboxID)\n    }\n    \n    // Remove finalizer\n    controllerutil.RemoveFinalizer(ar, AgentRuntimeFinalizer)\n    _, err := r.client.AgentRuntimes(ar.Namespace).Update(ctx, ar, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    return Result{Requeue: true}, err\n}\n```\n\n### Work Queue with Rate Limiting\n\n```go\n// NewRateLimitedWorkQueue creates a workqueue with exponential backoff.\nfunc NewRateLimitedWorkQueue(name string) workqueue.RateLimitingInterface {\n    return workqueue.NewRateLimitingQueue(\n        workqueue.NewItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter(\n            100*time.Millisecond, // base delay\n            5*time.Minute,        // max delay\n        ),\n    )\n}\n\n// Worker loop\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) runWorker() {\n    for r.processNextItem() {\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) processNextItem() bool {\n    key, quit := r.workqueue.Get()\n    if quit {\n        return false\n    }\n    defer r.workqueue.Done(key)\n    \n    result, err := r.Reconcile(context.Background(), key.(string))\n    if err != nil {\n        if result.TerminalError {\n            r.workqueue.Forget(key)\n            klog.Errorf(\"Terminal error reconciling %s: %v\", key, err)\n        } else {\n            r.workqueue.AddRateLimited(key)\n        }\n        return true\n    }\n    \n    if result.Requeue {\n        if result.RequeueAfter > 0 {\n            r.workqueue.AddAfter(key, result.RequeueAfter)\n        } else {\n            r.workqueue.AddRateLimited(key)\n        }\n        return true\n    }\n    \n    r.workqueue.Forget(key)\n    return true\n}\n```\n\n### Phase State Machine\n\n```\n                    ┌──────────┐\n    CR Created ────►│ Pending  │\n                    └────┬─────┘\n                         │ Pod created\n                         ▼\n                    ┌──────────┐\n         ┌─────────│ Running  │◄────────┐\n         │         └────┬─────┘         │\n         │              │                │\n         │ Pod succeeds/│ Pod fails      │ Update\n         │ completes    │                │\n         ▼              ▼                │\n    ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐         │\n    │Succeeded │   │  Failed  │─────────┘\n    └──────────┘   └──────────┘\n```\n\n### Metrics\n\n```go\nvar (\n    reconcileTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_reconcile_total\",\n            Help: \"Total number of reconciliations\",\n        },\n        []string{\"controller\", \"result\"},\n    )\n    \n    reconcileLatency = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n        prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name:    \"agentcube_reconcile_latency_seconds\",\n            Help:    \"Reconciliation latency in seconds\",\n            Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n        },\n        []string{\"controller\"},\n    )\n    \n    workqueueDepth = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n        prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_workqueue_depth\",\n            Help: \"Current depth of the work queue\",\n        },\n        []string{\"controller\"},\n    )\n)\n```\n\n### Error Handling and Requeue Strategy\n\n| Error Type | Requeue | Backoff | Action |\n|------------|---------|---------|--------|\n| Get CR failed (not found) | No | N/A | Object deleted, ignore |\n| Get CR failed (other) | Yes | Yes | Retry with exponential backoff |\n| Pod creation failed | Yes | Yes | Update status to Failed, retry |\n| Pod update failed | Yes | Yes | Retry |\n| Status update failed | Yes | Yes | Retry (CR may be outdated) |\n| Store sync failed | Yes | No | Log warning, retry immediately |\n| Finalizer conflict | Yes | Yes | Update and requeue |\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files created/modified\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/controller.go` | ~250 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_reconciler.go` | ~300 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_reconciler.go` | ~280 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go` | ~100 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/queue.go` | ~80 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/finalizer.go` | ~60 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/metrics.go` | ~100 | New |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/types.go` | ~80 | New |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| WorkloadManager HTTP server | Controller provides CR status for API responses |\n| Store (Redis) | Controller syncs session state |\n| Garbage Collector | Coordinates finalizer-based cleanup |\n| Metrics pipeline | Scrapes controller metrics |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None for existing APIs**: This is new functionality\n- **client-go integration**: Depends on generated client in `client-go/` directory\n- **Compatibility**: Uses standard Kubernetes controller patterns\n- **CRD changes**: If CRD spec changes, reconciler logic must be updated\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Use controller-runtime instead of generated client-go\n\n**Approach**: Use `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` framework with its manager, reconciler, and event source abstractions.\n\n**Rejected because**: The project already uses generated client-go with informers (as specified in client-go.md). controller-runtime adds significant dependency overhead and abstracts away the cache behavior we need to control. The generated client-go approach provides better performance tuning for high-frequency reconciliation.\n\n### 2. Use dynamic client instead of typed client\n\n**Approach**: Use `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` for unstructured CR access.\n\n**Rejected because**: Typed clients provide compile-time type safety, better IDE support, and cleaner code. The generated client-go library is already available, making the dynamic client unnecessary. Type safety is important for maintaining CR status schema consistency.\n\n### 3. Single reconciler for both CR types\n\n**Approach**: Implement one generic reconciler that handles both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter.\n\n**Rejected because**: The two CR types have different specs, status structures, and reconciliation logic. A generic reconciler would require significant reflection/type assertion, making the code harder to maintain. Separate reconcilers allow type-specific optimizations and clearer separation of concerns.\n\n### 4. Reconcile via polling instead of informers\n\n**Approach**: Periodically list all CRs and reconcile them instead of using informer events.\n\n**Rejected because**: Polling creates unnecessary API server load and introduces latency between CR changes and reconciliation. Informers provide efficient event-driven reconciliation with local caching, which is the standard Kubernetes pattern.\n\n### 5. Handle all CRDs in one workqueue\n\n**Approach**: Use a single workqueue for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter reconcilers.\n\n**Rejected because**: Different CR types may have different priorities and rate limits. Separate workqueues allow independent tuning and prevent one CR type from starving the other. This also provides better observability through per-controller metrics.\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Typed client for runtime/v1alpha1 |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Core Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s API machinery (schema, runtime) |\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` | v0.34.1 | Generated client dependency |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics collection |\n| Store (Redis/Valkey) | - | Session state sync |\n| AR-004 HTTP Framework | - | Provides HTTP handlers that read CR status |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/...\n\n# Integration tests with fake clientset\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconciler\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -run \"TestCodeInterpreterReconciler\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -run \"TestControllerManager\"\n\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/...\n\n# Verify metrics endpoint\ncurl http://localhost:8080/metrics | grep agentcube_reconcile\n\n# Verify race conditions\ngo test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/...\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-004](#ar-004--http-service-framework) — HTTP Service Framework\n- [AR-006](#ar-006--sandbox-deletion-and-lifecycle-management) — Sandbox Lifecycle Management\n- [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) — Generated client details\n- [Kubernetes Controller Pattern](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/controller/) — Controller design principles\n- [client-go Informers](https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/informers) — Informer documentation\n- [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md) — Status and condition patterns\n\n---\n\n*AR-007 — Module: pkg/workloadmanager — Language: Go — Size: L*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775850989105,"end":1775850989180}}}}
