{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850995047,"sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","part":{"id":"prt_d78f7b8dd001HYO3W9N7Jf8DDy","messageID":"msg_d78f7a6b0001I5lRCLPxp58P6W","sessionID":"ses_2870b075cffeswj069rRIYV7w1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler Controller\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller in `pkg/workloadmanager` that watches and reconciles `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources. This controller uses the generated client-go library to provide robust, event-driven reconciliation of sandbox lifecycle states, ensuring the actual state of sandbox pods matches the desired state defined in the CRs.\n6: \n7: The reconciler handles CR creation, updates, and deletion events; manages Pod lifecycle through the Kubernetes API; updates CR status with observed state; and implements requeue logic for transient failures. It integrates with the WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework (AR-004) and provides the core control loop for the AgentCube platform.\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Scope\n12: \n13: ### In scope\n14: \n15: | Item | Detail |\n16: |------|--------|\n17: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n18: | **CRDs managed** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) |\n19: | **Controller types** | `AgentRuntimeReconciler`, `CodeInterpreterReconciler` |\n20: | **Core functionality** | Event-driven reconciliation, status updates, Pod lifecycle management, finalizer handling, requeue with backoff |\n21: | **Integration with** | client-go generated clientset (typed client), informers (cache), Store (Redis) for session sync |\n22: | **Error handling** | Requeue on transient errors, permanent failure marking, exponential backoff, rate limiting |\n23: \n24: ### Out of scope\n25: \n26: - CRD definition and schema (already defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`)\n27: - client-go library generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n28: - HTTP server framework itself (AR-004)\n29: - Store implementation details (external dependency)\n30: - Multi-cluster reconciliation\n31: - Custom metrics server (separate component)\n32: - Webhook validation/mutation (separate AR)\n33: - Helm chart modifications\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Design\n38: \n39: ### File layout\n40: \n41: | File | Role |\n42: |------|------|\n43: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/controller.go` | **NEW** — Controller manager, shared informer factory setup, graceful shutdown |\n44: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_reconciler.go` | **NEW** — `AgentRuntimeReconciler` implementation |\n45: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_reconciler.go` | **NEW** — `CodeInterpreterReconciler` implementation |\n46: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go` | **NEW** — Base `Reconciler` interface and common utilities |\n47: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/queue.go` | **NEW** — Rate-limited work queue with exponential backoff |\n48: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/finalizer.go` | **NEW** — Finalizer management utilities |\n49: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/metrics.go` | **NEW** — Reconciliation metrics (attempts, latency, errors) |\n50: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/types.go` | **NEW** — Controller-specific type definitions |\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 488. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler Controller\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller in `pkg/workloadmanager` that watches and reconciles `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources. This controller uses the generated client-go library to provide robust, event-driven reconciliation of sandbox lifecycle states, ensuring the actual state of sandbox pods matches the desired state defined in the CRs.\n\nThe reconciler handles CR creation, updates, and deletion events; manages Pod lifecycle through the Kubernetes API; updates CR status with observed state; and implements requeue logic for transient failures. It integrates with the WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework (AR-004) and provides the core control loop for the AgentCube platform.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| **CRDs managed** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) |\n| **Controller types** | `AgentRuntimeReconciler`, `CodeInterpreterReconciler` |\n| **Core functionality** | Event-driven reconciliation, status updates, Pod lifecycle management, finalizer handling, requeue with backoff |","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775850995036,"end":1775850995045}}}}
